<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: How to open explorer without showing subfolders as a def]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=505&amp;p=2631#p2631"><![CDATA[
Don't delete anything, just hide it. You can do a few tricks in Explorer to clean up the navigation pane:<br /><br />1. From Tools menu -&gt; Folder Options: General tab You can uncheck the option &quot;Show all folders&quot; so a lot of unnecessary folders get hidden.<br />2. In Folder Options: View tab: Check the option: Hide empty drives in the Computer folder.<br />3. Right-click the individual libraries (Documents, Pictures etc) and choose &quot;Don't show in navigation pane&quot; so only the parent &quot;Libraries&quot; item gets shown.<br />4. To completely hide special items like Libraries, Homegroup, Network, if you don't need them in the navigation pane, you can use a tool like Windows 7 Navigation Pane Customizer: <a href="http://www.door2windows.com/windows-7-navigation-pane-customizer-show-hide-rename-items-in-windows-explorer-navigation-pane/" class="postlink">http://www.door2windows.com/windows-7-navigation-pane-customizer-show-hide-rename-items-in-windows-explorer-navigation-pane/</a><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Thu Apr 11, 2013 12:06 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
